{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3e4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"844"},"text":"§ 844.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Art. 44. Former jeopardy","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3e5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" No person may, without his consent, be tried a second time for the same offense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3e6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" No proceeding in which an accused has been found guilty by a court-martial upon any charge or specification is a trial in the sense of this article until the finding of guilty has become final after review of the case has been fully completed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3e7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3e8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A court-martial with a military judge alone is a trial in the sense of this section (article) if, without fault of the accused—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3e9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" after introduction of evidence; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3ea-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" before announcement of findings under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s853"},"text":"section 853 of this title","children":[],"tail":" (article 53);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the case is dismissed or terminated by the convening authority or the special trial counsel or on motion of the prosecution for failure of available evidence or witnesses.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3eb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A court-martial with a military judge and members is a trial in the sense of this section (article) if, without fault of the accused—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3ec-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" after the members, having taken an oath as members under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s842"},"text":"section 842 of this title","children":[],"tail":" (article 42) and after completion of challenges under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s841"},"text":"section 841 of this title","children":[],"tail":" (article 41), are impaneled; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3ed-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s844/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" before announcement of findings under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s853"},"text":"section 853 of this title","children":[],"tail":" (article 53);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the case is dismissed or terminated by the convening authority or the special trial counsel or on motion of the prosecution for failure of available evidence or witnesses.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida81cb3ee-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/52"},"text":"70A Stat. 52","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/dE/tLVII/s5226"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328, div. E, title LVII, § 5226","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/2910"},"text":"130 Stat. 2910","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/dA/tV/s538"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title V, § 538","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/1698"},"text":"135 Stat. 1698","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida81cb3ef-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"ida81cb3f0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"ida81cb3f1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-